Singapore
Publish Start Date
Mar 27 2014
Job Level
Experienced (Non-Manager)
|
Responsibilities:
Our graduate program, AP Sales Academy, is a 12 month program within one of Emerson’s business units, Fisher, which is one of the industry leaders in the control valves business.
In this program, you will have the opportunity to work along with and be trained by our industry experts on supporting the sales channels in product selection, technical specification, pricing and Industry solution.  An opportunity to work with other pillars of the sales stakeholders together with the sales channels to develop industry situation knowledge and application know-how to meet both the business and customer expectations.
You will undergo a comprehensive program which includes an induction that comprises of core curriculum modules to set a strong foundation for technical and business understanding, a series of rotational attachments to various functions, including short-term overseas attachment, as well as exposure to cross-functional teams.
Requirements:
As a technology and manufacturing company, we are especially interested in Engineering Degree graduates majoring in Mechanical / Instrumentation/ Chemical Engineering, with not more than 2 years of working experience, for this sales academy program.
The successful candidate will be someone with strong technical aptitude, customer focus, drive for results.  He/she should also possess good priority setting and interpersonal and communication skills with the ability to interact with internal and external stakeholders and adaptable in a complex work environment. Some relevant experience or knowledge in the process control industry will be advantageous.
If you want to take on new and meaningful challenges, grow professionally, and be part of a global organization committed to excellence, it's time to consider joining our dynamic team.